==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Top-hamper
<hw>Top"-ham`per</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Naut.)</fld>
<def>The upper rigging, spars, etc., of a ship.</def> <altsp>[Written
also <asp>top hamper</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>All the ships of the fleet . . . were so encumbered with
<qex>tophamper</qex>, so overweighted in proportion to their draught of
water, that they could bear but little canvas, even with smooth seas and
light and favorable winds.</q> <rj><qau>Motley.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Top-heavy</ent>⟦br⟧
